344,'http://blinkmortgageutah.com/344-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(508,1,'2017-06-13 00:41:26','2017-06-13 06:41:26','[et_pb_section bb_built=\"1\" admin_label=\"section\"][et_pb_row admin_label=\"row\"][et_pb_column type=\"4_4\"][et_pb_text admin_label=\"Text\" background_layout=\"light\" text_orientation=\"center\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\n<h1>Learn about the lenguage we use in our industry</h1>\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row admin_label=\"Row\"][et_pb_column type=\"1_2\"][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Amortization\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nThe paying off of debt with a fixed repayment schedule in regular installments over a period of time.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Appraisal\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nAn unbiased third-party opinion of a homes value based on factors including size of the home,\r\ntype of property, condition of the house, and the local real estate market.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"APR\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nThe annual percentage rate (APR) is a way to compare loan prices between lenders that takes\r\ninto account interest rate, points, and fees in the price of the loan. However, because there is no\r\nstandard for how this number is calculated - lenders have free reign on what to include in their\r\ncalculations making it a poor apples-to-apples comparison.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"ARM\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nAn adjustable rate mortage starts out with a fixed interest rate for a set period of time and then adjusts on a regular schedule after that with set interest rate caps. The loan term of an ARM\r\nis 30 years, but these mortgages are rarely held for the full term before the home is sold. In an example of 7/11 ARM. This interest fixed for seven years is fixed for seven years after which the rate will adjust every one year thereafter.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Closing Costs\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nExpenses unrelated to the cost of the property that buyers incur to complete a real estate\r\ntransaction. Closing costs can include loan origination fees, discount points, appraisal fees, title\r\nsearches, title insurance, taxes, deed-recording fees, and credit report charges.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Comps\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nAn abbreviation for comparables this terms refers to the home an appraiser looks at with\r\nsimilar characteristics in the same neighborhood to assess the true value of a home.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Conforming Mortgage\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nA loan meeting the requirement to be eligible for purchase by Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac\r\nincluding, but not exceeding $417,000 in traditional markets or $625,500 in high-cost markets.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Conventional Mortgage\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nConventional mortgages are all loans that are not made or guaranteed by the U.S. government\r\n(e.g. FHA, VA, USDA, etc.). Not all conventional loans are conforming but all conforming loans are\r\nconventional.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Debt-to-Income Ratio (DTI)\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nA personal finance measure that compares an individual\'s obligations to his or her overall income; lenders use this to measure an individuals ability to manage monthly mortgage\r\npayments.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Deed of Trust\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nA formal document pledging the house as collateral against your mortgage\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Down Payment\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nThe amount of money you put down in cash to purchase a home.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Escrow\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nA required part of the home closing process that involves depositing necessary funds,\r\ndocuments, and instructions into an account that is held and managed by a third-party until all conditions for the sale are validated and finalized.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"FHA Loan\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nA mortgage insured by the Federal Housing Administration (FHA). FHA loans are designed for\r\nlow to moderate income borrowers who are unable to make a large down payment or have a low credit score that makes it difficult to qualify for a conventional mortgage. FHA loans allow borrowers to put only 3.5% down on the home making them popular with first-time homebuyers.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Fixed-Rate Mortgage\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nThe interest rate of a fixed rate mortgage does not change over the life of the loan.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Home Equity\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nThe value of ownership built up in a home that represents the current market value of the house\r\nminus the remaining loan balance. This value is built up over time as the property owner pays off the mortgage and the market value of the property appreciates and represents one of the largest sources of net worth for most investors. Home equity can be borrowed against through a home equity loan or home equity line of credit.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type=\"1_2\"][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Home Inspection\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nA licensed home inspector does an examination of your future home and lets you know if there are any problems with the house that could affect its safety or resale value.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Homeowners Insurance\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nProperty insurance designed to protect an individuals home against damages to the house itself,\r\nor to possessions in the home. Homeowners insurance also provides liability coverage against\r\naccidents in the home or on the property.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Impounds\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nAn account maintained by mortgage companies to collect amounts such as hazard insurance,\r\nproperty taxes, private mortgage insurance and other required payments from mortgage\r\nborrowers. This is common in low down payment situations where the lender does not want to\r\nbe liable for these expenses should a borrower default. The lender uses an impounds account to\r\npay these charges monthly.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Interest Rate\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nThe percentage amount charged by a lender for a borrower to take out a loan.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Jumbo Loan\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nJumbo mortgages come into play in housing markets where property values are particularly high\r\nand a conforming mortgage is not large enough. Qualifying for a jumbo loan usually requires\r\nlower debt-to-income ratios, higher credit scores, larger down payments and higher emergency\r\nsaving funds than qualifying for a conforming loan.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Lender\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nThe bank, credit union, or other financial institution that provides the funding for your mortgage.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Loan Originator\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nAn institution or individual that works with a borrower to complete a mortgage transaction.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Loan-To-Value ratio (LTV)\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nThe LTV is calculated as mortgage amount divided by appraised value of the property. Typically, a\r\nhigher LTV is seen as a higher risk.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Mortgage Advisor\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nThe unbiased expert at Sindeo who guides you through the mortgage selection process, who knows tour complete financial picture, who helps you make the right decisions about home financing.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Mortgage Application\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nA document submitted by one or more individuals applying to borrow money to purchase a property. The data on this application - including personal financial information and property stats - is used to determine whether money should be lent to the applicants and if so, how much,\r\nfor how many years, and at what interest rate.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Mortgage Insurance\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nAn insurance policy that protects a mortgage lender or title holder in the event that the borrower\r\ndefaults on payments, dies, or is otherwise unable to meet the contractual obligations of the\r\nmortgage. Mortgage Insurance is often required if you are putting less than 20% down on your\r\nhome, including in the case of FHA loans.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Points\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nPoints give you the opportunity to lower your interest rate by providing an up front payment\r\n(called a mortgage buydown) or increase your interest rate in return for a credit that can be\r\nused towards closing costs (called a rebate). Each point is equal to 1% of total loan value - or\r\n$1,000 for every $100,000.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Principal\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nThe amount borrowed by a homebuyer before interest is added.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Promissory Note\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nSometimes just called a note, this is a formal document stating you promise to pay debts to\r\nyour lender as agreed.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"Term\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nThe life of your loan or the length of time it takes to fully pay back your loan. The term is selected\r\nprior to taking out a mortgage; a longer terms means lower monthly payments but more interest\r\npaid over time.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"USDA Loan\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nThe US Department of Agriculture offers a variety of loans to help borrowers buy homes in rural areas. USDA mortgages are structured just like conventional mortgages, but they have no down payment requirement. This means homebuyers can finance a home for 100% of its purchase price. However, the USDA will assess a two percent mortgage insurance fee to all loans.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][et_pb_toggle admin_label=\"Toggle\" title=\"VA Loan\" open=\"off\" use_border_color=\"off\" border_color=\"#ffffff\" border_style=\"solid\"]\r\n\r\nVA loans are offered by landers approved by the department of veterans affairs (VA). VA loans have lower down payment requirements, sometimes as low as zero. In addition, these loans often have lower interest rates and do not require mortgage insurance. To qualify for a VA loan, you must be a current member or veteran of the U.S. Armed Forces or an eligible surviving spouse.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_toggle][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]','lingo','','publish','closed','closed','','lingo','','','2017-06-13 00:41:26','2017-06-13 06:41:26','',0,'http://blinkmortgageutah.com/?page_id=508',0,'page','',0),(507,1,'2017-06-13 00:07:33','2017-06-13 06:07:33','[et_pb_section fb_built=\"1\" custom_padding=\"96px|0px|0px|0px\" admin_label=\"section\"][et_pb_row make_fullwidth=\"on\" use_custom_gutter=\"on\" gutter_width=\"1\" background_image=\"http://blinkmortgageutah.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/qtq50